I think maybe what's confusing you, is if you wanted to know the torques in a fixed inertial frame, you'd have to break them down into ijk components, which you could do. A little tedious. But the answers in this one came out in r hat, theta hat, k hat terms. Happy to answer. This is good stuff, but thick. So keep-- other questions?

